{"subject":"Economics",'year':2000,"question":"National income is the:",'options':['Total value of goods and services produced in an economy in a year','Total wealth of a country','Government budget','Money supply'],'correctIndex':0,"explanation":"National income measures output over a period."},
{"subject":"Economics",'year':2001,"question":"The expenditure method of measuring national income sums:",'options':['Consumption, investment, government spending, net exports','Incomes of factors','Value added in each sector','Taxes and transfers'],'correctIndex':0,"explanation":"Expenditure approach: GDP = C + I + G + (X - M)."},
